column1: There have been changes to the recording of self directed support in the Referrals, Assessments and Packages of Care (RAP) return which has impacted on the production of unit costs within the PSS-EX1.  Specifically, clients receiving council commissioned services via a personal budget were only captured under the personal budget/direct payment activity line in RAP and not under the service they received such as home care.  This has caused a mismatch between the activity data in RAP and the expenditure data in PSSEX as the expenditure will be assigned to home care and therefore a unit cost can not be calculated.
A list of unit costs that will not be present in the PSS-EX1 UCS Table for 2009-10
